abstract: The police charged a Des Moines woman with attempted murder after she told investigators she intentionally ran over a 14-year-old girl with her vehicle.
snippet: The police charged a Des Moines woman with attempted murder after she told investigators she intentionally ran over a 14-year-old girl with her vehicle.
lead_paragraph: An Iowa woman was charged with attempted murder after running over a 14-year-old girl because she thought the teenager was Mexican, the police said.

abstract: The discovery of human remains at the Alamo introduced another point of friction in a $450 million renovation project that has been fraught with disagreements over the site’s complex history.
snippet: The discovery of human remains at the Alamo introduced another point of friction in a $450 million renovation project that has been fraught with disagreements over the site’s complex history.
lead_paragraph: The remains of three people were uncovered during excavation work at the Alamo in San Antonio, and the discovery has reignited longstanding disputes over how to tell the full history of one of the most fabled battle sites in the United States.

abstract: The illness that swept through the England camp has eased with bowlers Jofra Archer, Stuart Broad and Jack Leach returning to training as Ollie Pope struck a century in the three-day warm-up fixture against South Africa A in Benoni on Saturday.
snippet: The illness that swept through the England camp has eased with bowlers Jofra Archer, Stuart Broad and Jack Leach returning to training as Ollie Pope struck a century in the three-day warm-up fixture against South Africa A in Benoni on Saturday.
lead_paragraph: JOHANNESBURG — The illness that swept through the England camp has eased with bowlers Jofra Archer, Stuart Broad and Jack Leach returning to training as Ollie Pope struck a century in the three-day warm-up fixture against South Africa A in Benoni on Saturday.
headline_main: Pope Hits Ton for England as Trio Overcome Illness to Train
headline_print_headline: Pope Hits Ton for England as Trio Overcome Illness to Train

abstract: A collision between a passenger bus and a trailer truck in eastern Guatemala early on Saturday killed at least 20 people, including a 7-year-old boy, doctors and firefighters said.
snippet: A collision between a passenger bus and a trailer truck in eastern Guatemala early on Saturday killed at least 20 people, including a 7-year-old boy, doctors and firefighters said.
lead_paragraph: GUATEMALA CITY — A collision between a passenger bus and a trailer truck in eastern Guatemala early on Saturday killed at least 20 people, including a 7-year-old boy, doctors and firefighters said.
headline_main: At Least 20 Dead in Bus Crash in Eastern Guatemala
headline_print_headline: At Least 20 Dead in Bus Crash in Eastern Guatemala

abstract: Democratic presidential candidate Pete Buttigieg encountered tough questions and some skepticism about how he'd help end racial disparities in policing as he worked to reach out to Nevada's communities of color Saturday.
snippet: Democratic presidential candidate Pete Buttigieg encountered tough questions and some skepticism about how he'd help end racial disparities in policing as he worked to reach out to Nevada's communities of color Saturday.
lead_paragraph: LAS VEGAS — Democratic presidential candidate Pete Buttigieg tackled issues of racial disparity as he met with Nevada's communities of color Saturday, though the small-town Indiana mayor encountered tough questions and skepticism from some voters.
headline_main: Buttigieg Playing Catchup in Reaching Nevada Voters of Color
headline_print_headline: Buttigieg Playing Catchup in Reaching Nevada Voters of Color

abstract: In a county jail in central Texas, an inmate on suicide watch begins strangling himself with a phone cord. The guard watching him does not rush in because of security rules that prohibit him from going into a cell alone, leading to an agonizing 10-minute wait before another staffer arrives to provide backup.

abstract: Cartoonist Jim Davis is offering up more than 11,000 “Garfield” comic strips hand-drawn on paper in an auction that will stretch into the coming years, with at least a couple of strips featuring the always-hungry orange cat with a sardonic sense of humor available weekly.
snippet: Cartoonist Jim Davis is offering up more than 11,000 “Garfield” comic strips hand-drawn on paper in an auction that will stretch into the coming years, with at least a couple of strips featuring the always-hungry orange cat with a sardonic sense o...
lead_paragraph: DALLAS — Cartoonist Jim Davis is offering up more than 11,000 “Garfield” comic strips hand-drawn on paper in an auction that will stretch into the coming years, with at least a couple of strips featuring the always-hungry orange cat with a sardonic sense of humor available weekly.
headline_main: 30-Plus Years of ‘Garfield’ Comic Strips to Sell at Auction
headline_print_headline: 30-Plus Years of ‘Garfield’ Comic Strips to Sell at Auction

abstract: A growing community near Kansas City has decided to stop publishing its legal notices in its hometown newspaper, describing the move as cost cutting but doing it after several officials criticized the coverage the city was receiving.
snippet: A growing community near Kansas City has decided to stop publishing its legal notices in its hometown newspaper, describing the move as cost cutting but doing it after several officials criticized the coverage the city was receiving.
lead_paragraph: TOPEKA, Kan. — A growing community near Kansas City has decided to stop publishing its legal notices in its hometown newspaper, describing the move as cost cutting but doing it after several officials criticized the coverage the city was receiving.
headline_main: Kansas City's Move Against Paper Strikes Some as Retaliation
headline_print_headline: Kansas City's Move Against Paper Strikes Some as Retaliation

abstract: France's President Emmanuel Macron has vowed to boost the fight against Islamic extremism in West Africa as French troops killed 33 Islamic extremists in central Mali.
snippet: France's President Emmanuel Macron has vowed to boost the fight against Islamic extremism in West Africa as French troops killed 33 Islamic extremists in central Mali.
lead_paragraph: ABIDJAN, Ivory Coast — France's President Emmanuel Macron has vowed to boost the fight against Islamic extremism in West Africa as French troops killed 33 Islamic extremists in central Mali.
headline_main: Macron Vows to Keep Fighting Extremism in West Africa
headline_print_headline: Macron Vows to Keep Fighting Extremism in West Africa
